			<description>It is coming and it will change society in ways that are good, bad. Will the good outweigh the bad? 
 
Been thinking about this tech for a while now. No particular article or news story prompted this, it is just something that has been rummaging around my mind.  
 
Some of the good things - no...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>It is coming and it will change society in ways that are good, bad. Will the good outweigh the bad?<br />
<br />
Been thinking about this tech for a while now. No particular article or news story prompted this, it is just something that has been rummaging around my mind. <br />
<br />
Some of the good things - no wasted time during your commute. Take a nap or read a book. Less or No accidents. No mandatory insurance because if a human isn't driving then he can't be at fault. Gramma can still go out shopping and won't wreck her car. Heck, kids can now be chauffered by Google.<br />
<br />
The bad things include - No privacy about where you go. Talk about a dataminers wet dream. No mandatory insurance - lots of people will lose their jobs and rich people will lose their capital gains. Limits on where people can &quot;drive&quot; set arbitrarily or for profit. Need to keep people away from that G20 meeting, presto chango no one can drive near it. How easy would it be to disappear some one? As soon as victim enters car - doors lock and drive to warehouse. Imagine the chaos if the system went belly up during &quot;rush hour&quot;?<br />
<br />
Discuss.<br />
<br />
ps PTotD - Paranoid Thought of the Day.</div>

