			<title>Not sure what to call this</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?76935-Not-sure-what-to-call-this&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Tue, 17 Jun 2014 19:12:35 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[I couldn't really figure out what to call the other thread either. Thread titles can be tough to come up with at times. I have gone back and forth about posting this here.  
 
A few of you already know this but I am terminally ill. I have Idiopathic Pulmonary Fibrosis among other things wrong with...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I couldn't really figure out what to call the other thread either. Thread titles can be tough to come up with at times. I have gone back and forth about posting this here. <br />
<br />
A few of you already know this but I am terminally ill. I have Idiopathic Pulmonary Fibrosis among other things wrong with me. I created a thread on the flight sim forums about it. It's a fairly long and detailed thread. If you are interested at all, at least read the first post. Please remember that the thread was started in November of 2012. According to what I have read, that 50% of the people with pulmonary fibrosis are dead within 2 years. So I am pretty sure I will be above average. At least unless things go really bad in the next couple of months. <br />
<br />
<a href="http://simhq.com/forum/ubbthreads.php/topics/3799328/1" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://simhq.com/forum/ubbthreads.php/topics/3799328/1</a><br />
<br />
I have another PET/CT scan and PFT test on Monday. My pulmonologist told me on Thursday that my PET/CT scans keep showing some really ugly stuff but when they did the bronchoscopy it was a negative result. It didn't make a lot of sense to him. So this time if it shows up the same or worse, that they will probably do a medical biopsy. He is still concerned about cancer and on the last one, I had a node on my adrenal gland and he was upset my primary didn't follow up on it. He want's to look at that one too to see if it has changed at all. <br />
<br />
If you read the other thread, note that it was a progression over time, so look at the post dates. I tried to post my thoughts as honestly as I could. I will do my best to answer any questions anyone has. I am sure the first question will be &quot;Why am I posting this?&quot; <br />
<br />
I had told someone here and he told a couple of others. I am not upset that he did because his heart was in the right place. I am ok with that although immediately, I was upset, but got over it in a couple of hours. A few people from here went over there and posted in the thread and at that point I decided to let the thread die. (Pun Intended) I struggled a bit with the decision to post it here, but figured it would be better to be in control of how information is getting out. <br />
<br />
There is a lot of personal information in the other thread, but please don't use it in any negative way. I left it in because I wanted people to know it was real. It's an interesting read in my opinion. My state of mind is very clear in the thread and it hasn't changed. <br />
<br />
So I will leave it at that and don't hesitate to ask anything you want to know.<br />
<br />
Edit: Please no pity posts or I am sorry you are sick posts or anything like that. It's not why I posted it.</div>

